ðŸ”¹ Example (Neo4j â€“ Cypher)
CREATE (u:User {name: "Shoaib"})
CREATE (p:Product {name: "Laptop"})
CREATE (u)-[:BOUGHT]->(p)


Query:

MATCH (u:User)-[:BOUGHT]->(p)
RETURN u.name, p.name;

ðŸ”¹ When Should YOU Use a Graph DB?

Use a graph DB if:

Relationships matter more than raw data

You have many-to-many connections

You run deep traversal queries

You want recommendations or network insights

Avoid it if:

Data is simple & tabular

Mostly CRUD operations

ðŸ”¹ One-line definition

A graph database stores data as nodes and relationships, making relationship-heavy queries fast and intuitive.
